Ah, I see! You're trying to run:
on a **Debian i386 system** (32-bit Intel), but NodeSource does **not support i386** builds anymore — only `amd64`, `arm64`, and `armhf`.
---
### 🧨 Why it's not working
NodeSource officially dropped support for **i386 architecture**, so their setup script won't add the right repo. That’s why you're getting an error or nothing is installed after the script runs.
---
### ✅ Solution: Install Node.js 20+ on i386 manually
We’ll use **Node.js official binaries** compiled for `linux-ia32` (i386).
---
### 🛠️ Step-by-Step Manual Install on i386
#### 1. Remove old Node.js (if any):
```bash
sudo apt remove nodejs npm -y
``
#### 2. Download prebuilt Node.js binary for i386
```bash
cd ~
wget https://nodejs.org/dist/v20.14.0/node-v20.14.0-linux-ia32.tar.xz
```
You can check for newer versions here: [https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v20.x/](https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v20.x/)
#### 3. Extract and install manually:
```bash
tar -xf node-v20.14.0-linux-ia32.tar.xz
sudo mv node-v20.14.0-linux-ia32 /opt/node20
```
#### 4. Add Node.js to your PATH:
Append this line to your `~/.bashrc` or `~/.profile`:
```bash
export PATH=/opt/node20/bin:$PATH
```
Then reload:
```bash
source ~/.bashrc
```
#### 5. Verify installation:
```bash
node -v
npm -v
```
You should see:
``
v20.14.0
```

---

